
Extract parts of a string:

var str = "Hello world!";
var res = str.slice(1,5);
The result of res will be:

//ello


The slice() method extracts parts of a string and returns the extracted parts in a new string.

Use the start and end parameters to specify the part of the string you want to extract.

Tip: Use a negative number to select from the end of the string.

Syntax
string.slice(start,end)


Parameter	Description
start	Required. The position where to begin the extraction.
end	Optional. The position (up to, but not including) where to end the extraction. If omitted, slice() selects
all characters from the start-position to the end of the string.

Return Value:	A String, representing the extracted part of the string


                                                Example

Extract the whole string:

var str = "Hello world!";
var res = str.slice(0);
console.log(res);

// Hello world!


                                                Example

Extract only the last character:

var str = "Hello world!";
var res = str.slice(-1);
console.log(res);

// !

